anings":["English and Irish (of Norman origin): variant of   Molyneux  . Compare   Mallonee  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":5,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":30,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":43,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Molyneux of Netherton was born about 1285, in Rainhill, Lancashire, England as the son of Robert Molyneux. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1285–":"umbes 1285–Surnud","1285–Male":"1285–Surnud","1318–Male":"1318–Surnud","1264–1336":"1264–1336","1315":"1315","1336":"1336","1264":"1264","1285":"1285","1318":"1318","about 1285":"umbes 1285","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Rainhill, Lancashire, England":"Rainhill, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"about 1285–":"noin 1285–Kuollut","1285–Male":"1285–Kuollut","1318–Male":"1318–Kuollut","1264–1336":"1264–1336","1315":"1315","1336":"1336","1264":"1264","1285":"1285","1318":"1318","about 1285":"noin 1285","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Rainhill, Lancashire, England":"Rainhill, Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"about 1285–":"environ 1285–Décédé","1285–Male":"1285–Décédé","1318–Male":"1318–Décédé","1264–1336":"1264–1336","1315":"1315","1336":"1336","1264":"1264","1285":"1285","1318":"1318","about 1285":"environ 1285","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Rainhill, Lancashire, England":"Rainhill, Lancashire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Robert Molyneux of Netherton est né environ 1285, à Rainhill, Lancashire, Angleterre, fils de Robert Molyneux. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"about 1285–":"um 1285–Verstorben","1285–Male":"1285–Verstorben","1318–Male":"1318–Verstorben","1264–1336":"1264–1336","1315":"1315","1336":"1336","1264":"1264","1285":"1285","1318":"1318","about 1285":"um 1285","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Rainhill, Lancashire, England":"Rainhill, Lancashire, England","lifeSummary":"Robert Molyneux of Netherton wurde um 1285 in Rainhill, Lancashire, England, als Sohn von Robert Molyneux geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"about 1285–":"about 1285–Desede","1285–Male":"1285–Desede","1318–Male":"1318–Desede","1264–1336":"1264–1336","1315":"1315","1336":"1336","1264":"1264","1285":"